# docs/ai trust tiers (agents)

Full policy: `docs/ai/templates/DOC_GOVERNANCE.md` §5. Human backlog: `docs/ai/ACTIVE_WORK.md`.

## Tier A — planning sources (may drive work)

- `docs/ai/PROJECT_CONTEXT.md`
- `docs/ai/PROGRESS_LOG.md` (recent entries only)
- `docs/ai/BOOTSTRAP_DIGEST.md`
- `docs/ai/ACTIVE_WORK.md`
- `docs/ai/FEATURE_REGISTRY.md` — **In Progress** or **Planned** only
- `docs/ai/TECH_DEBT.md` — **Open** rows only
- User-named design with Meta Status `In Progress` or `Review`

## Tier B — reference only (do not build backlog from)

- `docs/course/` — PDF and reference images
- Designs with Status Done / Snapshot / Archived / Reference
- Unchecked checklists in old docs
- `docs/ai/sessions/`

## Tier C — code is truth

If Tier A/B disagrees with **RTL**, **simulation waves**, or **`verify.ps1` results**:

1. Trust code + verification for current behavior.
2. State doc may be stale; do not treat gaps as mandatory work unless user or ACTIVE_WORK asks.

## Conflicts

| Situation | Resolution |
|-----------|------------|
| Doc vs RTL/sim | RTL + verify |
| Doc vs user this session | User |
| ACTIVE_WORK vs course PDF | ACTIVE_WORK |
| FEATURE_REGISTRY Planned vs no ACTIVE_WORK | Ask user |

## New work

Register in FEATURE_REGISTRY; update ACTIVE_WORK when user wants agent-visible priority.
